oc:kn_3998a06e a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining cohorts or segments for comparative analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never define segments using the outcome variable being measured — use pre-treatment characteristics instead to avoid circular logic (selection bias)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Segmenting by outcome creates tautological conclusions that are unfalsifiable and misleading." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5273505f a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When producing any analysis intended for stakeholder consumption" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every non-trivial analysis must document: the specific question being answered, data sources with as-of dates, metric/segment definitions, methodology steps, assumptions and limitations, and all queries used." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Documentation ensures reproducibility, enables peer review, and protects against misinterpretation of results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6527c3e5 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When combining data from multiple sources with timestamp fields" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Standardize all timestamps to a single timezone (UTC recommended) before analysis and document the timezone used, to prevent misalignment between data sources." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Timezone mismatches cause silent date misalignment that shifts events between periods, corrupting time-series analysis." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_69bfb010 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning any data validation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before running validation, confirm: data sources are identified, 'as of' date is known, metric definitions are documented, and the analysis question is clearly stated." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Validation without understanding what is being validated wastes time and may miss the most important issues." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6f743982 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When making period-over-period comparisons" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never compare partial periods to full periods (e.g., month-to-date vs. prior full month) without adjusting for completeness." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incomplete period comparison makes trends appear worse or better than reality, misleading stakeholders." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_8d6b92e2 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When validating any analysis before sharing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Run validation in sequence: 1) Review methodology and assumptions → 2) Pre-delivery QA checklist → 3) Check analytical pitfalls → 4) Verify calculations → 5) Assess visualizations → 6) Evaluate narrative → 7) Suggest improvements → 8) Generate confidence assessment." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The sequential workflow ensures comprehensive coverage from methodology through presentation, preventing oversight of any validation dimension." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b418c737 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When sanity-checking any analytical result" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Apply the 'smell test': verify magnitude (numbers in plausible range), cross-validate (calculate same metric two ways), and watch for red flags (>50% unexplained changes, exact round numbers, 0%/100% rates, results too perfect)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Quick heuristic checks catch the majority of data errors before they reach stakeholders." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b912e565 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When issues are found during validation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If validation finds issues, fix them and re-validate. Share the validation output alongside the analysis to build stakeholder confidence." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Iterative validation catches cascading errors, and transparency about the validation process strengthens credibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_f31e704a a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing or reviewing SQL queries with JOINs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Check row counts before and after JOINs to detect many-to-many join explosion that silently inflates counts and sums." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Many-to-many joins multiply rows without error, making it the most common silent data error in analytical work." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_feee0c48 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When aggregating metrics across segments with unequal sizes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never average pre-computed averages when group sizes differ — always aggregate from raw data to avoid the 'average of averages' error." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Averaging averages ignores group weighting, producing mathematically incorrect results that can be dramatically off from the true mean." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

